Valuable team member, the new Data Analyst will play an important role in our team, by preparing internal (local and regional) reports, providing clarity on our results to our internal and external partners and leveraging data to increase process and cost efficiency.




Key Responsibilities:




Make essential data available to our internal and external partners, by creating reports and dashboards, with the use of technical skills and business knowledge (to obtain and evaluate the data, but also by reviewing the insights the data provides).
Help remove obstacles in Customer Service & Operations activity during execution of change management projects or small fixes, by using business and system/ technical knowledge to help build and implement workflows, using available technology (Microsoft Power automate, Power Apps).




Detailed responsibilities will include:




Create quantitative and qualitative reports for the Service & Operations Department on a monthly and quarterly basis;
Communicate with other departments to provide input for Operations Department reports;
Ensure inputs to evaluate the CS & Operations Department's KPI’s;
Ensure consistency and justification of reported values in cooperation with other departments;
Communicate and collaborate with Company Headquarters and regional structures on reporting, planning and CR (change requests for target metrics and/or reported metrics);
Update and set up processes and procedures at the Operations Department level;
Create ad-hoc reports;
Support projects implementation, by contributing to development of suitable business requirements, testing scenarios and testing activities;
Provide information to end users to help resolve problems regarding assigned system(s);
Contribute to user guides, reference manuals and training materials;
Actively participate in change management activities - build and implement workflows, using available technology (Microsoft Power automate, Power Apps).




The Data Analyst we are looking for requires both hard and soft skills to excel in the position, at least:




Hard Skills

Bachelor's degree;
Good understanding of operational processes, including knowledge of managing data/ technology processes, acquired in a job in insurance operations (1-2 years’ experience);
Friends with technology and systems: knowledge of one or more of our administration system/ systems (preferable CLAS, Telemark) is considered a plus;
Very good English knowledge;
Proven proficiency in Microsoft Office (especially Excel);
SQL/Power Automate /Power Apps Knowledge – are considered a plus;
Ability to maintain effectiveness and professionalism when experiencing change in work tasks and/or the work environment.




Soft Skills

Interpersonal skills: the ability to interact and build effective working relationships with peers and all levels of management;
Strong data analytical skills: you must be able to leverage on data and statistical tools to draw valid conclusions and solve business problems (Data Cleaning & Preparation – obtain data from one or more sources, tackling missing and unstable data that may impact the assessment, Data Analysis and Exploration, Building Dashboards and Developing Data Visualizations - developing clean, visually compelling reports and graphs that will help others comprehend the data);
Communication skills: The job of a Data Analyst is a cross-functional role that requires communication and teamwork with all other departments; so it is essential that you have oral and written communication skills to work effectively with others;
Problem solving skills: Being a data analyst, you will face problems, bugs, or bottlenecks each day. The critical skill is to find ways to solve the problem and move ahead;
Enthusiasm for Knowledge and Development - this is a team where we learn and develop together and being eager to improve/diversify your skills will help us deliver exceptional results.




We value your work, by offering:




Friendly environment with multiple career development opportunities;
Inclusive and multicultural team where you can create impact with your innovative ideas and creative personality;
Various learning & development programs adapted to your needs and goals;
Benefits (flexible hours, meal tickets, private medical subscription, insurance policy, Bookster subscription, additional holidays based on seniority, annual performance bonus, holiday bonus, etc);
Excellent location – close to public transport stations (bus & subway) & hybrid way of working.




